listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing â€” do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** â€” fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale â‡’ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` â€” repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` â€” open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` â€” operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` â€” blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** â€” out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch â€” meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact â€” DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** â€” the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator â€” do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-71005284\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eregistry: honor package skill source and target mappings\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  Package installs declare skill source/target mappings in `package.yaml`, but the remote package installer does not apply those mappings. The plan requires `install.skills[*].source` to be honored relative to the package root and child skill directories to be installed under each target without replacing unrelated skills.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  cli/internal/registry/installer.go:110-132 ignores `pkg.Install.Skills` mapping sources and targets by calling `skills.Install(os.DirFS(absExtracted), absProject, ...)`, then guesses installed skill names with `recordInstalledSkills`. cli/internal/registry/installer.go:191-218 also hard-codes `.agents/skills` and `skills` as discovery roots and always records `.agents/skills` plus `.claude/skills`, regardless of manifest targets. The plan\u0026#39;s manifest contract at docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout.md:77-100 requires mapping-driven install behavior.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/registry/installer.go: add a shared helper that applies every `InstallMapping` in `pkg.Install.Skills` from the extracted/package root to the mapping target.\u0026#xA;  - Keep directory-to-directory semantics: `source: skills/`, `target: .agents/skills/` copies or records each child skill directory, such as `skills/ddx -\u0026gt; .agents/skills/ddx`, and does not replace `.agents/skills` itself.\u0026#xA;  - Update installed-file recording to reflect actual mapping targets.\u0026#xA;  - Add focused registry tests for manifest skill source/target behavior and preservation of unrelated existing project skills.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Local `--local` symlink overlays; a sibling bead owns that path.\u0026#xA;  - `ddx init` routing through an embedded default package; a sibling bead owns that path.\u0026#xA;  - Moving the DDx skill tree into `library/skills/ddx`; a later bead owns the content move.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PARENT + DEPS\u0026#xA;  Parent: ddx-6862f2ac. No deps.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestInstallPackageHonorsSkillSource` proves a fixture with `install.skills.source: skills/` installs `skills/ddx/SKILL.md` to `.agents/skills/ddx/SKILL.md` and `.claude/skills/ddx/SKILL.md` without needing `.agents/skills` inside the source package.\u0026#xA;2. `TestInstallPackagePreservesUnrelatedProjectSkills` proves installing a package skill mapping does not delete or replace an existing unrelated skill directory under `.agents/skills` or `.claude/skills`.\u0026#xA;3. `TestInstallPackageRecordsManifestSkillTargets` proves `InstalledEntry.Files` contains the actual project-relative child skill paths produced by the mapping targets.\u0026#xA;4. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/registry/... -run \u0026#39;TestInstallPackageHonorsSkillSource|TestInstallPackagePreservesUnrelatedProjectSkills|TestInstallPackageRecordsManifestSkillTargets\u0026#39; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;5. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/registry/...` passes.\u0026#xA;6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:plugins, area:skills, area:cli, kind:feature, plan-2026-05-13, spec:plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-6862f2ac\" spec-id=\"plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\" base-rev=\"534c54b1ba0ed4c0d8c696966398610397a6e57c\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout.md\"\u003eDDx Skill Package Layout\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260513T183521-176c69d0","base_rev":"534c54b1ba0ed4c0d8c696966398610397a6e57c","bead_id":"ddx-71005284","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260513T183521-176c69d0","correlation_id":"ddx-71005284:20260513T183521